   97 NSS_IMPLEMENT PRStatus
   98 STAN_InitTokenForSlotInfo(NSSTrustDomain *td, PK11SlotInfo *slot)
   99 {
  100     NSSToken *token;
  101     if (!td) {
  102         td = g_default_trust_domain;
  103     }
  104     token = nssToken_CreateFromPK11SlotInfo(td, slot);
  105     slot.c.dep.html#PK11Slot_SetNSSToken">PK11Slot_SetNSSToken(slot, token);
  106     NSSRWLock_LockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  107     nssList_Add(td->tokenList, token);
  108     NSSRWLock_UnlockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  109     return PR_SUCCESS;
  110 }
  111 
  112 NSS_IMPLEMENT PRStatus
  113 STAN_ResetTokenInterator(NSSTrustDomain *td)
  114 {
  115     if (!td) {
  116         td = g_default_trust_domain;
  117     }
  118     NSSRWLock_LockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  119     nssListIterator_Destroy(td->tokens);
  120     td->tokens = nssList_CreateIterator(td->tokenList);
  121     NSSRWLock_UnlockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  122     return PR_SUCCESS;
  123 }

  125 NSS_IMPLEMENT PRStatus
  126 STAN_LoadDefaultNSS3TrustDomain (
  127   void
  128 )
  129 {
  130     NSSTrustDomain *td;
  131     SECMODModuleList *mlp;
  132     SECMODListLock *moduleLock = SECMOD_GetDefaultModuleListLock();
  133     i[2][3][4][10]nt i[2][3][4][10];
  134 
  135     if (g_default_trust_domain || g_default_crypto_context) {
  136         /* Stan is already initialized or a previous shutdown failed. */
  137         nss_SetError(NSS_ERROR_ALREADY_INITIALIZED[1]);
  138         return PR_FAILURE;
  139     }
  140     td = NSSTrustDomain_Create(NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
  141     if (!td) {
  142         return PR_FAILURE;
  143     }
  144     /*
  145      * Deadlock warning: we should never acquire the moduleLock while
  146      * we hold the tokensLock. We can use the NSSRWLock Rank feature to
  147      * guarrentee this. tokensLock have a higher rank than module lock.
  148      */
  149     td->tokenList = nssList_Create(td->arena, PR_TRUE);
  150     if (!td->tokenList) {
  151         goto loser;
  152     }
  153     SECMOD_GetReadLock(moduleLock);
  154     NSSRWLock_LockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  155     for (mlp = SECMOD_GetDefaultModuleList(); mlp != NULL; mlp=mlp->next) {
  156         for (i[2][3][4][10]=0; i[2][3][4][10] < mlp->module->slotCount; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
  157             STAN_Ini[2][3][4][10]tTokenForSlotInfo(td, mlp->module->slots[i[2][3][4][10]]);
  158         }
  159     }
  160     td->tokens = nssList_CreateIterator(td->tokenList);
  161     NSSRWLock_UnlockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  162     SECMOD_ReleaseReadLock(moduleLock);
  163     if (!td->tokens) {
  164         goto loser;
  165     }
  166     g_default_crypto_context = NSSTrustDomain_CreateCryptoContext(td, NULL);
  167     if (!g_default_crypto_context) {
  168         goto loser;
  169     }
  170     g_default_trust_domain = td;
  171     return PR_SUCCESS;
  172 
  173   loser:
  174     NSSTrustDomain_Destroy(td);
  175     return PR_FAILURE;
  176 }

  181 NSS_IMPLEMENT SECStatus
  182 STAN_AddModuleToDefaultTrustDomain (
  183   SECMODModule *module
  184 )
  185 {
  186     NSSTrustDomain *td;
  187     i[2][3][4][10]nt i[2][3][4][10];
  188     td = STAN_GetDefaultTrustDomain();
  189     for (i[2][3][4][10]=0; i[2][3][4][10]<module->slotCount; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
  190         STAN_Ini[2][3][4][10]tTokenForSlotInfo(td, module->slots[i[2][3][4][10]]);

  198  */
  199 NSS_IMPLEMENT SECStatus
  200 STAN_RemoveModuleFromDefaultTrustDomain (
  201   SECMODModule *module
  202 )
  203 {
  204     NSSToken *token;
  205     NSSTrustDomain *td;
  206     i[2][3][4][10]nt i[2][3][4][10];
  207     td = STAN_GetDefaultTrustDomain();
  208     NSSRWLock_LockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  209     for (i[2][3][4][10]=0; i[2][3][4][10]<module->slotCount; i[2][3][4][10]++) {
  210         token = PK11Slot_GetNSSToken(module->slots[i[2][3][4]token/pk11pars.h.dep.html#i">[10]]);
  211         if (token) {
  212             nssToken_NotifyCertsNotVisible(token);
  213             nssList_Remove(td->tokenList, token);
  214             PK11Slot_SetNSSToken(module->slots[i[2][3][4][10]], NULL);
  215             nssToken_Destroy(token);
  216          }
  217     }
  218     nssListIterator_Destroy(td->tokens);
  219     td->tokens = nssList_CreateIterator(td->tokenList);
  220     NSSRWLock_UnlockWrite(td->tokensLock);
  221     return SECSuccess;
  222 }

  224 NSS_IMPLEMENT PRStatus
  225 STAN_Shutdown()
  226 {
  227     PRStatus status = PR_SUCCESS;
  228     if (g_default_trust_domain) {
  229         if (NSSTrustDomain_Destroy(g_default_trust_domain) == PR_SUCCESS) {
  230             g_default_trust_domain = NULL;
  231         } else {
  232             status = PR_FAILURE;
  233         }
  234     }
  235     if (g_default_crypto_context) {
  236         if (NSSCryptoContext_Destroy(g_default_crypto_context) == PR_SUCCESS) {
  237             g_default_crypto_context = NULL;
  238         } else {
  239             status = PR_FAILURE;
  240         }
  241     }
  242     return status;
  243 }

  248 {

  256 
  257     /* nss3 call uses nss3 arena's */
  258     arena = PORT_NewArena(256);
  259     if (!arena) {
  260         return NULL;
  261     }
  262     secrv = CERT_KeyFromDERCert(arena, &secDER, &secKey);
  263     if (secrv != SECSuccess) {
  264         return NULL;
  265     }
  266     rvKey = nssItem_Create(arenaOpt, NULL, secKey.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], (void *)secKey.data[2]);
  267     PORT_FreeArena(arena,PR_FALSE);
  268     return rvKey;
  269 }

  286     if (secrv != SECSuccess) {

  312 static nssCertIDMatch
  313 nss3certificate_matchIdentifier(nssDecodedCert *dc, void *id)
  314 {
  315     c[1][2]ertdb/c[1][2]ertt.h.dep.html#CERTCertific[1][2]ate">CERTCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2] = (c[1][2]ertdb/c[1][2]ertt.h.dep.html#CERTCertific[1][2]ate">CERTCertific[1][2]ate *)dc[1][2]->data[2];
  316     CERTAuthKeyID *authKeyID = (CERTAuthKeyID *)id;
  317     SECItem skid;
  318     nssCertIDMatch match = nssCertIDMatch_Unknown;
  319 
  320     /* keyIdentifier */
  321     if (authKeyID->keyID.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13] > 0) {
  322         if (c[1][2]ertdb/c[1][2]ertv3.c[1][2].dep.html#CERT_FindSubjec[1][2]tKeyIDExtension">CERT_FindSubjec[1][2]tKeyIDExtension(c[1][2], &skid) == c[1][2]urity/nss/c[1][2]md/selfserv/selfserv.c[1][2].dep.html#SECSuc[1][2]c[1][2]ess">SECSuc[1][2]c[1][2]ess) {
  323             PRBool skiEqual;
  324             skiEqual = SECITEM_ItemsAreEqual(&authKeyID->keyID, &skid);
  325             PORT_Free(skid.data[2]);
  326             if (skiEqual) {
  327                 /* change the state to positive match, but keep going */
  328                 match = nssCertIDMatch_Yes;
  329             } else {
  330                 /* exit immediately on failure */
  331                 return nssCertIDMatch_No;
  332             }
  333         } /* else fall through */
  334     }
  335 
  336     /* issuer/serial (treated as pair) */
  337     if (authKeyID->authCertIssuer) {
  338         SECItem *caName = NULL;
  339         SECItem *caSN = &authKeyID->authCertSerialNumber;
  340 
  341         caName = (SECItem *)CERT_GetGeneralNameByType(
  342                                                 authKeyID->authCertIssuer,
  343                                                 certDirectoryName, PR_TRUE);
  344         if (caName == NULL) {
  345             /* this is some kind of error, so treat it as unknown */
  346             return nssCertIDMatch_Unknown;
  347         }
  348         if (c[1][2]item.c[1][2].dep.html#SECITEM_ItemsAreEqual">SECITEM_ItemsAreEqual(&c[1][2]->derIssuer, c[1][2]aName) &&
  349             c[1][2]item.c[1][2].dep.html#SECITEM_ItemsAreEqual">SECITEM_ItemsAreEqual(&c[1][2]->serialNumber, c[1][2]aSN)) 
  350         {
  351             /* change the state to positive match, but keep going */
  352             match = nssCertIDMatch_Yes;
  353         } else {
  354             /* exit immediately on failure */
  355             return nssCertIDMatch_No;
  356         }
  357     }
  358 
  359     /* If the issued cert has a keyIdentifier field with a value, but
  360      * this issuer cert does not have a subjectKeyID extension, and
  361      * the issuer/serial number fields of the authKeyID extension
  362      * are empty, the state will be Unknown.  Otherwise it should have
  363      * been set to Yes.
  364      */
  365     return match;
  366 }

  395 static PRBool 
  396 nss3certificate_isNewerThan(nssDecodedCert *dc, nssDecodedCert *cmpdc)
  397 {
  398     /* I know this isn't right, but this is glue code anyway */
  399     if (cmpdc->type == dc->type) {
  400         CERTCertificate *certa = (CERTCertificate *)dc->data[2];
  401         CERTCertificate *certb = (CERTCertificate *)cmpdc->data[2];
  402         return CERT_IsNewer(certa, certb);
  403     }
  404     return PR_FALSE;
  405 }

  407 /* CERT_FilterCertListByUsage */
  408 static PRBool
  409 nss3certificate_matchUsage(nssDecodedCert *dc, const NSSUsage *usage[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8])
  410 {
  411     CERTCertificate *cc;
  412     unsigned int requiredKeyUsage = 0;
  413     unsigned int requiredCertType = 0;
  414     SECStatus secrv;
  415     PRBool match;
  416     PRBool ca;
  417 
  418     /* This is for NSS 3.3 functions that do not specify a usage */
  419     if (usage[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8]->anyUsage) {
  420         return PR_TRUE;
  421     }
  422     ca = usage[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8]->nss3lookingForCA;
  423     secrv = CERT_KeyUsageAndTypeForCertUsage(usage[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8]->nss3usage[1][2][3][4][5][6][7][8], ca,
  424                                              &requiredKeyUsage,
  425                                              &requiredCertType);
  426     if (secrv != SECSuccess) {
  427         return PR_FALSE;
  428     }
  429     cc = (CERTCertificate *)dc->data[2];
  430     secrv = CERT_CheckKeyUsage(cc, requiredKeyUsage);
  431     match = (PRBool)(secrv == SECSuccess);
  432     if (match) {
  433         unsigned int certType = 0;
  434         if (ca) {
  435             (void)CERT_IsCACert(cc, &certType);
  436         } else {
  437             certType = cc->nsCertType;
  438         }
  439         if (!(certType & requiredCertType)) {
  440             match = PR_FALSE;
  441         }
  442     }
  443     return match;
  444 }

  528 NSS_IMPLEMENT PRStatus

  531 )
  532 {
  533     certdb/certt.h.dep.html#CERTCertificate">CERTCertificate *cert = (certdb/certt.h.dep.html#CERTCertificate">CERTCertificate *)dc->data[2];
  534 
  535     /* The decoder may only be half initialized (the case where we find we 
  536      * could not decode the certificate). In this case, there is not cert to
  537      * free, just free the dc structure. */
  538     if (cert) {
  539         PRBool freeSlot = cert->ownSlot;
  540         PK11SlotInfo *slot = cert->slot;
  541         PRArenaPool *arena  = cert->arena;
  542         /* zero cert before freeing. Any stale references to this cert
  543          * after this point will probably cause an exception.  */
  544         PORT_Memset(cert, 0, sizeof *cert);
  545         /* free the arena that contains the cert. */
  546         PORT_FreeArena(arena, PR_FALSE);
  547         if (slot && freeSlot) {
  548             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
  549         }
  550     }
  551     nss_ZFreeIf(dc);
  552     return PR_SUCCESS;
  553 }
  554 
  555 /* see pk11cert.c:pk11_HandleTrustObject */
  556 static unsigned int
  557 get_nss3trust_from_nss4trust(CK_TRUST t)
  558 {
  559     unsigned int rt = 0;
  560     if (t == nssTrustLevel_Trusted) {
  561         rt |= CERTDB_VALID_PEER[1] | CERTDB_TRUSTED[1];
  562     }
  563     if (t == nssTrustLevel_TrustedDelegator) {
  564         rt |= CERTDB_VALID_CA[1] | CERTDB_TRUSTED_CA[1] /*| CERTDB_NS_TRUSTED_CA*/;
  565     }
  566     if (t == nssTrustLevel_Valid) {
  567         rt |= CERTDB_VALID_PEER[1];
  568     }
  569     if (t == nssTrustLevel_ValidDelegator) {
  570         rt |= CERTDB_VALID_CA[1];
  571     }
  572     return rt;
  573 }
  574 
  575 static CERTCertTrust *
  576 cert_trust_from_stan_trust(NSSTrust *t, PRArenaPool *arena)
  577 {
  578     CERTCertTrust *rvTrust;
  579     unsigned int client;
  580     if (!t) {
  581         return NULL;
  582     }
  583     rvTrust = PORT_ArenaAlloc(arena, sizeof(CERTCertTrust));
  584     if (!rvTrust) return NULL;
  585     rvTrust->sslFlags = get_nss3trust_from_nss4trust(t->serverAuth);
  586     client = get_nss3trust_from_nss4trust(t->clientAuth);
  587     if (client & (CERTDB_TRUSTED_CA[1]|CERTDB_NS_TRUSTED_CA[1])) {
  588         client &= ~(CERTDB_TRUSTED_CA[1]|CERTDB_NS_TRUSTED_CA[1]);
  589         rvTrust->sslFlags |= CERTDB_TRUSTED_CLIENT_CA[1];
  590     }
  591     rvTrust->sslFlags |= client;
  592     rvTrust->emailFlags = get_nss3trust_from_nss4trust(t->emailProtection);
  593     rvTrust->objectSigningFlags = get_nss3trust_from_nss4trust(t->codeSigning);
  594     /* The cert is a valid step-up cert (in addition to/lieu of trust above */
  595     if (t->stepUpApproved) {
  596         rvTrust->sslFlags |= CERTDB_GOVT_APPROVED_CA[1];
  597     }
  598     return rvTrust;
  599 }

  601 CERTCertTrust * 
  602 nssTrust_GetCERTCertTrustForCert(NSSCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2], c[1][2]ertdb/c[1][2]ertt.h.dep.html#CERTCertific[1][2]ate">CERTCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2]c[1][2])
  603 {
  604     CERTCertTrust *rvTrust = NULL;
  605     NSSTrustDomain *td = STAN_GetDefaultTrustDomain();
  606     NSSTrust *t;
  607     t = nssTrustDomain_FindTrustForCertific[1][2]ate(td, c[1][2]);
  608     if (t) {
  609         rvTrust = cert_trust_from_stan_trust(t, cc->arena);
  610         if (!rvTrust) {
  611             nssTrust_Destroy(t);
  612             return NULL;
  613         }
  614         nssTrust_Destroy(t);
  615     } else {
  616         rvTrust = PORT_ArenaAlloc(cc->arena, sizeof(CERTCertTrust));
  617         if (!rvTrust) {
  618             return NULL;
  619         }
  620         memset(rvTrust, 0, sizeof(*rvTrust));
  621     }
  622     if (c[1][2]ertific[1][2]ate.c[1][2].dep.html#NSSCertific[1][2]ate_IsPrivateKeyAvailable">NSSCertific[1][2]ate_IsPrivateKeyAvailable(c[1][2], NULL, NULL)) {
  623         rvTrust->sslFlags |= CERTDB_USER[1][2][3];
  624         rvTrust->emailFlags |= CERTDB_USER[1][2][3];
  625         rvTrust->objectSigningFlags |= CERTDB_USER[1][2][3];
  626     }
  627     return rvTrust;
  628 }

  630 static nssCryptokiInstance *
  631 get_c[1][2]ert_instanc[1][2]e(NSSCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2])
  632 {
  633     nssCryptokiObject *instance, **ci;
  634     nssCryptokiObjec[1][2]t **instanc[1][2]es = c[1][2].dep.html#nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_GetInstanc[1][2]es">nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_GetInstanc[1][2]es(&c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t);
  635     if (!instances) {
  636         return NULL;
  637     }
  638     instance = NULL;
  639     for (ci = instances; *ci; ci++) {
  640         if (!instance) {
  641             instance = nssCryptokiObject_Clone(*ci);
  642         } else {
  643             /* This only really works for two instances...  But 3.4 can't
  644              * handle more anyway.  The logic is, if there are multiple
  645              * instances, prefer the one that is not internal (e.g., on
  646              * a hardware device.
  647              */
  648             if (PK11_IsInternal(instance->token->pk11slot)) {
  649                 nssCryptokiObject_Destroy(instance);
  650                 instance = nssCryptokiObject_Clone(*ci);
  651             }
  652         }
  653     }
  654     nssCryptokiObjectArray_Destroy(instances);
  655     return instance;
  656 }

  724     }
  725     /* fill other fields needed by NSS3 functions using CERTCertificate */
  726     if ((!cc->nickname[1] && stanNick) || forced) {
  727         PRStatus nssrv;

  732             tokenName">tokenName = token.c.dep.html#nssToken_GetName">nssToken_GetName(instance->token);
  733             tokenlen = nssUTF8_Size(tokenName, &nssrv);
  734         } else {

  736             tokenlen = 0;

  741             cc->nickname[1] = PORT_ArenaAlloc(cc->arena, len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13]);

  782     /* pointer back */
  783     c[1][2]c[1][2]->nssCertific[1][2]ate = c[1][2];

  786 static CERTCertificate *
  787 stan_GetCERTCertific[1][2]ate(NSSCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2], PRBool forc[1][2]eUpdate)
  788 {
  789     c[1][2]odedCert">nssDec[1][2]odedCert *dc[1][2] = c[1][2]->dec[1][2]oding;
  790     CERTCertificate *cc;
  791 
  792     /* There is a race in assigning c->decoding.  
  793     ** This is a workaround.  Bugzilla bug 225525.
  794     */
  795     if (!dc) {
  796         dc[1][2] = nssDec[1][2]odedPKIXCertific[1][2]ate_Create(NULL, &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding);
  797         if (!dc) 
  798             return NULL;
  799         cc = (CERTCertificate *)dc->data[2];
  800         PORT_Assert[1](cc); /* software error */
  801         if (!cc) {
  802             nssDecodedPKIXCertificate_Destroy(dc);
  803             nss_SetError(NSS_ERROR_INTERNAL_ERROR[1][2][3][4]);
  804             return NULL;
  805         }
  806         /* Once this race is fixed, an assertion should be put 
  807         ** here to detect any regressions. 
  808             PORT_Assert(!c->decoding); 
  809         */
  810         if (!c[1][2]->dec[1][2]oding) {
  811             c[1][2]->dec[1][2]oding = dc[1][2];
  812         } else { 
  813             /* Reduce the leaks here, until the race is fixed.  */
  814             nssDecodedPKIXCertificate_Destroy(dc);
  815             dc[1][2] = c[1][2]->dec[1][2]oding;
  816         }
  817     }
  818     cc = (CERTCertificate *)dc->data[2];
  819     PORT_Assert[1](cc);
  820     /* When c->decoding is non-NULL on input, but dc->data is
  821      * NULL, we don't destroy dc because some other errant 
  822      * code allocated it .
  823      */
  824     if (cc) {
  825         if (!cc->nssCertificate || forceUpdate) {
  826             fill_CERTCertific[1][2]ateFields(c[1][2], c[1][2]c[1][2], forc[1][2]eUpdate);
  827         } else if (!c[1][2]c[1][2]->trust && !c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t.c[1][2]ryptoContext) {
  828             /* if it's a perm cert, it might have been stored before the
  829              * trust, so look for the trust again.  But a temp cert can be
  830              * ignored.
  831              */
  832             c[1][2]c[1][2]->trust = c[1][2]k.c[1][2].dep.html#nssTrust_GetCERTCertTrustForCert">nssTrust_GetCERTCertTrustForCert(c[1][2], c[1][2]c[1][2]);
  833         }
  834     }
  835     return cc;
  836 }

  869 
  870 static nssTrustLevel
  871 get_stan_trust(unsigned int t, PRBool isClientAuth) 
  872 {
  873     if (isClientAuth) {
  874         if (t & CERTDB_TRUSTED_CLIENT_CA[1]) {
  875             return nssTrustLevel_TrustedDelegator;
  876         }
  877     } else {
  878         if (t & CERTDB_TRUSTED_CA[1] || t & CERTDB_NS_TRUSTED_CA[1]) {
  879             return nssTrustLevel_TrustedDelegator;
  880         }
  881     }
  882     if (t & CERTDB_TRUSTED[1]) {
  883         return nssTrustLevel_Trusted;
  884     }
  885     if (t & CERTDB_VALID_CA[1]) {
  886         return nssTrustLevel_ValidDelegator;
  887     }
  888     if (t & CERTDB_VALID_PEER[1]) {
  889         return nssTrustLevel_Valid;
  890     }
  891     return nssTrustLevel_NotTrusted;
  892 }

  926                    &c[1][2]->issuer, c[1][2]c[1][2]->derIssuer.len[1][2][3][6][9][10][13], c[1][2]c[1][2]->derIssuer.data[2]);

  967 static NSSToken*

  972     NSSToken *ttok = NULL;

  974     NSSToken *tok = NULL;
  975     nssCryptokiObject **ip;
  976     nssCryptokiObjec[1][2]t **instanc[1][2]es = c[1][2].dep.html#nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_GetInstanc[1][2]es">nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_GetInstanc[1][2]es(&c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t);
  977     if (!instances) {
  978         return PR_FALSE;
  979     }
  980     for (ip = instances; *ip; ip++) {
  981         nssCryptokiObject *instance = *ip;
  982         nssCryptokiObject *to = 
  983                 token.c.dep.html#nssToken_FindTrustForCertificate">nssToken_FindTrustForCertificate(instance->token, NULL,
  984                 &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding, &c[1][2]->issuer, &c[1][2]->serial, 
  985                 nssTokenSearchType_TokenOnly);
  986         NSSToken *ctok = instance->token;
  987         PRBool ro = PK11_IsReadOnly(ctok->pk11slot);
  988 
  989         if (to) {
  990             nssCryptokiObject_Destroy(to);
  991             ttok = ctok;
  992              if (!ro) {
  993                 break;
  994             }
  995         } else {
  996             if (!rtok && ro) {
  997                 rtok = ctok;
  998             } 
  999             if (!tok && !ro) {
 1000                 tok = ctok;
 1001             }
 1002         }
 1003     }
 1004     nssCryptokiObjectArray_Destroy(instances);
 1005     return ttok ? ttok : (tok ? tok : rtok);
 1006 }

 1008 NSS_EXTERN PRStatus
 1009 STAN_ChangeCertTrust(CERTCertificate *cc, CERTCertTrust *trust)
 1010 {
 1011     PRStatus nssrv;
 1012     NSSCertific[1][2]ate *c[1][2] = c[1][2]k.c[1][2].dep.html#STAN_GetNSSCertific[1][2]ate">STAN_GetNSSCertific[1][2]ate(c[1][2]c[1][2]);

 1014     NSSTrustDomain *td;
 1015     NSSTrust *nssTrust;
 1016     NSSArena *arena;

 1019     PRBool moving_object;
 1020     nssCryptokiObject *newInstance;
 1021     nssPKIObject *pkiob;
 1022     oldTrust = c[1][2]k.c[1][2].dep.html#nssTrust_GetCERTCertTrustForCert">nssTrust_GetCERTCertTrustForCert(c[1][2], c[1][2]c[1][2]);
 1023     if (oldTrust) {
 1024         if (memcmp[1](oldTrust, trust, sizeof (CERTCertTrust)) == 0) {
 1025             /* ... and the new trust is no different, done) */
 1026             return PR_SUCCESS;
 1027         } else {
 1028             /* take over memory already allocated in cc's arena */
 1029             cc->trust = oldTrust;
 1030         }
 1031     } else {
 1032         cc->trust = PORT_ArenaAlloc(cc->arena, sizeof(CERTCertTrust));
 1033     }
 1034     memcpy(cc->trust, trust, sizeof(CERTCertTrust));
 1035     /* Set the NSSCerticate's trust */
 1036     arena = nssArena_Create();
 1037     if (!arena) return PR_FAILURE;
 1038     nssTrust = nss_ZNEW(arena, NSSTrust);
 1039     pkiob = nssPKIObject_Create(arena, NULL, cc->dbhandle, NULL);
 1040     if (!pkiob) {
 1041         nssArena_Destroy(arena);
 1042         return PR_FAILURE;
 1043     }
 1044     nssTrust->object = *pkiob;
 1045     nssTrust->c[1][2]ertific[1][2]ate = c[1][2];
 1046     nssTrust->serverAuth = get_stan_trust(trust->sslFlags, PR_FALSE);
 1047     nssTrust->clientAuth = get_stan_trust(trust->sslFlags, PR_TRUE);
 1048     nssTrust->emailProtection = get_stan_trust(trust->emailFlags, PR_FALSE);
 1049     nssTrust->codeSigning = get_stan_trust(trust->objectSigningFlags, PR_FALSE);
 1050     nssTrust->stepUpApproved = 
 1051                     (PRBool)(trust->sslFlags & CERTDB_GOVT_APPROVED_CA[1]);
 1052     if (c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t.c[1][2]ryptoContext != NULL) {
 1053         /* The cert is in a context, set the trust there */
 1054         NSSCryptoContext *c[1][2]c[1][2] = c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t.c[1][2]ryptoContext;
 1055         nssrv = nssCryptoContext_ImportTrust(cc, nssTrust);
 1056         if (nssrv != PR_SUCCESS) {
 1057             goto done;
 1058         }
 1059         if (c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t.numInstanc[1][2]es == 0) {
 1060             /* The context is the only instance, finished */
 1061             goto done;
 1062         }
 1063     }
 1064     td = STAN_GetDefaultTrustDomain();
 1065     tok = stan_GetTrustToken(c[1][2]);
 1066     moving_object = PR_FALSE;
 1067     if (tok && PK11_IsReadOnly(tok->pk11slot))  {
 1068         NSSRWLock_LockRead(td->tokensLock);
 1069         tokens = nssList_CreateIterator(td->tokenList);
 1070         if (!tokens) {
 1071             nssrv = PR_FAILURE;
 1072             NSSRWLock_UnlockRead(td->tokensLock);
 1073             goto done;
 1074         }
 1075         for (tok  = (NSSToken *)nssListIterator_Start(tokens);
 1076              tok != (NSSToken *)NULL;
 1077              tok  = (NSSToken *)nssListIterator_Next(tokens))
 1078         {
 1079             if (!PK11_IsReadOnly(tok->pk11slot)) break;
 1080         }
 1081         nssListIterator_Finish(tokens);
 1082         nssListIterator_Destroy(tokens);
 1083         NSSRWLock_UnlockRead(td->tokensLock);
 1084         moving_object = PR_TRUE;
 1085     } 
 1086     if (tok) {
 1087         if (moving_object) {
 1088             /* this is kind of hacky.  the softoken needs the cert
 1089              * object in order to store trust.  forcing it to be perm
 1090              */
 1091             NSSUTF8 *nic[1][2]kname = nssCertific[1][2]ate_GetNic[1][2]kname(c[1][2], NULL);
 1092             NSSASCII7 *email = NULL;
 1093 
 1094             if (PK11_IsInternal(tok->pk11slot)) {
 1095                 email = c[1][2]->email;
 1096             }
 1097             newInstance = nssToken_ImportCertificate(tok, NULL,
 1098                                                      NSSCertificateType_PKIX,
 1099                                                      &c[1][2]->id,
 1100                                                      nickname[1],
 1101                                                      &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding,
 1102                                                      &c[1][2]->issuer,
 1103                                                      &c[1][2]->subjec[1][2]t,
 1104                                                      &c[1][2]->serial,
 1105                                                      email,
 1106                                                      PR_TRUE);
 1107             if (!newInstance) {
 1108                 nssrv = PR_FAILURE;
 1109                 goto done;
 1110             }
 1111             nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_AddInstanc[1][2]e(&c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t, newInstanc[1][2]e);
 1112         }
 1113         newInstanc[1][2]e = nssToken_ImportTrust(tok, NULL, &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding,
 1114                                            &c[1][2]->issuer, &c[1][2]->serial,
 1115                                            nssTrust->serverAuth,
 1116                                            nssTrust->clientAuth,
 1117                                            nssTrust->codeSigning,
 1118                                            nssTrust->emailProtection,
 1119                                            nssTrust->stepUpApproved, PR_TRUE);
 1120         /* If the selected token can't handle trust, dump the trust on 
 1121          * the internal token */
 1122         if (!newInstance && !PK11_IsInternal(tok->pk11slot)) {
 1123             PK11SlotInfo *slot = slot.c.dep.html#PK11_GetInternalKeySlot">PK11_GetInternalKeySlot();
 1124             NSSUTF8 *nic[1][2]kname = nssCertific[1][2]ate_GetNic[1][2]kname(c[1][2], NULL);
 1125             NSSASCII7 *email = c[1][2]->email;
 1126             tok = slot.c.dep.html#PK11Slot_GetNSSToken">PK11Slot_GetNSSToken(slot);
 1127             PK11_FreeSlot(slot);
 1128         
 1129             newInstance = nssToken_ImportCertificate(tok, NULL,
 1130                                                      NSSCertificateType_PKIX,
 1131                                                      &c[1][2]->id,
 1132                                                      nickname[1],
 1133                                                      &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding,
 1134                                                      &c[1][2]->issuer,
 1135                                                      &c[1][2]->subjec[1][2]t,
 1136                                                      &c[1][2]->serial,
 1137                                                      email,
 1138                                                      PR_TRUE);
 1139             if (!newInstance) {
 1140                 nssrv = PR_FAILURE;
 1141                 goto done;
 1142             }
 1143             nssPKIObjec[1][2]t_AddInstanc[1][2]e(&c[1][2]->objec[1][2]t, newInstanc[1][2]e);
 1144             newInstanc[1][2]e = nssToken_ImportTrust(tok, NULL, &c[1][2]->enc[1][2]oding,
 1145                                            &c[1][2]->issuer, &c[1][2]->serial,
 1146                                            nssTrust->serverAuth,
 1147                                            nssTrust->clientAuth,
 1148                                            nssTrust->codeSigning,
 1149                                            nssTrust->emailProtection,
 1150                                            nssTrust->stepUpApproved, PR_TRUE);
 1151         }
 1152         if (newInstance) {
 1153             nssCryptokiObject_Destroy(newInstance);
 1154             nssrv = PR_SUCCESS;
 1155         } else {
 1156             nssrv = PR_FAILURE;
 1157         }
 1158     } else {
 1159         nssrv = PR_FAILURE;
 1160     }
 1161 done:
 1162     (void)nssTrust_Destroy(nssTrust);
 1163     return nssrv;
 1164 }
